  id: Humerus_R
  partName: Humerus Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - 'The right humerus is the main upper bone of the canine forelimb extending between
    the shoulder and elbow joints. It articulates proximally with the scapula and
    distally with the radius and ulna, forming essential joints for forelimb movement.
    This bone supports muscular attachment sites for muscles controlling '
  - shoulder and elbow motion during locomotion.The humerus contributes significantly
    to weight-bearing, propulsion, and shock absorption during walking, running,
    and jumping activities. Proper alignment and structural integrity are critical
    for efficient limb mechanics and stability.
